<div class="container">
    <h1>Privacy Policy for SatMon</h1>
    <p class="date">Last updated: January 30, 2026</p >

    <p>SatMon Team is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how our mobile application <strong>SatMon</strong> collects, uses, and shares your information. SatMon is a community-driven tool designed to monitor direct-to-cell satellite spectrum usage through crowdsourcing.</p >
    
    <p>By downloading and using SatMon, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.</p >

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We adhere to a principle of data minimization. We only collect the technical data necessary to identify and localize satellite transmitters and detect spectrum misuse. We do not collect any Personal Identifiable Information (PII).</p >

    <h3>A. Information You Provide to Us</h3>
    <p>We do not require you to create an account, provide your name, phone number, or email address to use the core features of the app.</p >

    <h3>B. Data Collected Automatically</h3>
    <p>When you use SatMon to perform a spectrum measurement, we collect the following technical data:</p >
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Location Data:</strong> We collect your device's precise geolocation (GPS coordinates) at the time of measurement. This is essential for calculating the "Round-Trip Time" (RTT) to satellites and for the geometric diversity required to accurately localize satellite transmitters.</li>
        <li><strong>Cellular Network Information:</strong> We access standard Android Telephony APIs to collect metadata about the cellular signal your device is receiving. This includes:
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Identifiers:</strong> Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN) code, Tracking Area Code (TAC), and Cell ID.</li>
                <li><strong>Signal Metrics:</strong> Timing Advance (TA), Signal-to-Interference-plus-Noise Ratio (SINR), Reference Signal Received Power (RSRP), and Reference Signal Received Quality (RSRQ).</li>
                <li><strong>Frequency Data:</strong> The RF band being used.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> We may collect basic device model information to calibrate measurements, as different chipsets may have varying performance.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. What We Do NOT Collect</h2>
    <p>To ensure your privacy and security:</p >
    <ul>
        <li><strong>No Communication Content:</strong> We never access, record, or store the content of your voice calls, SMS messages, or internet browsing history.</li>
        <li><strong>No Personal Identity:</strong> We do not collect data that links your device's measurements to your real-world identity.</li>
        <li><strong>No Root Access:</strong> SatMon operates entirely within the standard Android user permissions and does not request or require root privileges.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>The data collected is sent to our centralized data aggregator for the following purposes:</p >
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Satellite Identification & Localization:</strong> To calculate satellite fingerprints (specifically the uplink frame timing shift) and identify which satellite is transmitting signals.</li>
        <li><strong>Spectrum Monitoring:</strong> To detect if satellite operators are misusing licensed cellular bands or causing unauthorized interference.</li>
        <li><strong>Service Improvement:</strong> To refine our algorithms and improve the accuracy of satellite tracking.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Permissions Required</h2>
    <p>To function, SatMon requires the following permissions on your device:</p >
    <ul>
        <li><code>Location (ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION)</code>: Required to obtain the precise GPS coordinates needed for satellite orbital analysis.</li>
        <li><code>Phone State (READ_PHONE_STATE)</code>: Required to access cellular network information (like Cell ID and Timing Advance) via standard Telephony APIs.</li>
        <li><code>Internet</code>: Required to upload anonymized measurement reports to our server.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
    <p>We implement reasonable security measures to protect the data we collect. The data transmitted between your device and our aggregator is treated as technical research data.</p >

    <h2>6. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.</p >

    <h2>7. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:</p >
    <ul>
        <li>Email: <a href=" ">satmon217@gmail.com</a ></li>
    </ul>

